29/*! \brief Planning stage prior to rewriting in TransformLayoutRewriter
30 *
31 * There are four ways that transformation may be handled. Each
32 * updates the buffer shape and the indices used to acces the buffer
33 * in BufferStore/BufferLoad nodes, but differ in how they handle the
34 * `pad_value`. In order of preference, the different strategies are
35 * as follows:
36 *
37 * 1. NoPaddingRequired. The transformation does not introduce
38 * padding, so only local changes to update the indices of
39 * BufferLoad/BufferStore nodes are required. No blocks are added,
40 * removed, or replaced.
41 *
42 * 2. ProloguePlan. The transformation introduces padding, but the
43 * analyzed block has no write stages for the transformed buffer.
44 * This buffer is an input and the caller is responsible for ensuring
45 * that the padding contains the specified `pad_value`. The generated
46 * prologue contains `builtin::assume()` calls that will expose this
47 * known value during scheduling/simplification, but will be removed
48 * during lowering.
49 *
50 * 3. ReplacementPlan. The transformation introduces padding, has at
51 * least one write stage for the transformed buffer, and at least one
52 * of those write stages writes to all pre-transformation indices
53 * following a row-major traversal. These write stage is rewritten to
54 * be row-major traversals of the post-transformation indices, with a
55 * `tir::if_then_else` call to write either the specified `pad_value`
56 * into padding or the computed value into non-padding.
57 *
58 * 4. EpiloguePlan. The transformation introduces padding, has at
59 * least one write stage for the transformed buffer, but no write
60 * stage can be rewritten to use `tir::if_then_else`. The
61 * transformation still requires the `pad_value` to be written into
62 * the padding, so a new block is inserted after the last write stage
63 * to explicitly fill the padding.
64 *
65 */
66class TransformLayoutPlanner : private StmtExprVisitor {
67 public:
68 // Statement to be inserted prior to the analyzed block
69 struct ProloguePlan {
70 Stmt prologue;
71 };
72
73 // Loops within the analyzed block that should be replaced
74 struct ReplacementPlan {
75 Map<For, Stmt> replacements;
76 Map<Block, Block> block_sref_reuse;
77 };
78
79 // The block to be inserted, along with the location at which it
80 // should be inserted. The location will be either a For or a
81 // Block, and will be after all writes the transformed buffer.
82 struct EpiloguePlan {
83 Stmt insert_after;
84 Stmt new_block;
85 };
86
87 struct NoPaddingRequired {};
88
89 using TransformPlan =
90 std::variant<ProloguePlan, ReplacementPlan, EpiloguePlan, NoPaddingRequired>;
91
92 static TransformPlan Plan(Block block, Buffer old_buffer, Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
93 IndexMap inverse, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
94 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) {
95 ICHECK(!pad_value.defined() || pad_value.value()->final_indices.size() == 1)
96 << "Internal error: Should be caught by ScheduleError checks prior to this point";
97 TransformLayoutPlanner visitor(old_buffer);
98 visitor(block);
99 return visitor.Finalize(new_buffer, index_map, inverse, padding_predicate, pad_value);
100 }
101
102 private:
103 explicit TransformLayoutPlanner(Buffer old_buffer) : old_buffer_(old_buffer) {}
104
105 void VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) override {
106 BindLoopVar context(this, GetRef<For>(op));
107 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
108 }
109
110 void VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) override {
111 BindVariableDefinition context(this, op->var, op->value);
112 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
113 }
114
115 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) override {
116 BindBlockRealize context(this, GetRef<BlockRealize>(op));
117 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
118 }
119
120 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) override {
121 if (!op->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
122 return;
123 }
124
125 std::optional<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> loop_dependency_range = std::nullopt;
126 for (const auto& index : op->indices) {
127 if (auto index_depth = LoopDependencyRange(index); index_depth.has_value()) {
128 if (loop_dependency_range) {
129 loop_dependency_range = {
130 std::min(loop_dependency_range.value().first, index_depth.value().first),
131 std::max(loop_dependency_range.value().second, index_depth.value().second)};
132 } else {
133 loop_dependency_range = index_depth;
134 }
135 }
136 }
137
138 WriteInfo write_info;
139 write_info.store = GetRef<BufferStore>(op);
140 if (loop_dependency_range) {
141 size_t i = loop_dependency_range.value().first;
142 size_t j = loop_dependency_range.value().second;
143 ICHECK_LT(i, active_loops_.size());
144 ICHECK_LT(j, active_loops_.size());
145
146 write_info.dependent_loopnest = {active_loops_.begin() + i, active_loops_.begin() + j + 1};
147 }
148 write_info.innermost_block_realize = innermost_block_realize_;
149
150 write_info.contains_row_major_traversal = [&]() -> bool {
151 const auto& loopnest = write_info.dependent_loopnest;
152 if (loopnest.empty()) {
153 return false;
154 }
155
156 if (loopnest.size() != old_buffer_->shape.size() || loopnest.size() != op->indices.size()) {
157 return false;
158 }
159
160 for (size_t i = 0; i < loopnest.size(); i++) {
161 const For& loop = loopnest[i];
162 const PrimExpr& buffer_dim = old_buffer_->shape[i];
163 PrimExpr index = Substitute(op->indices[i], active_var_bindings_);
164 bool is_loop_over_axis = index.same_as(loop->loop_var) && is_const_int(loop->min, 0) &&
165 ExprDeepEqual()(loop->extent, buffer_dim) &&
166 loop->kind == ForKind::kSerial;
167 if (!is_loop_over_axis) {
168 return false;
169 }
170 }
171
172 return true;
173 }();
174
175 write_info_.push_back(write_info);
176
177 // Don't need to continue recursing, as the entire goal was to
178 // find the BufferStore.
179 }
180
181 std::optional<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> LoopDependencyRange(const PrimExpr& expr) const {
182 std::optional<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> prev = std::nullopt;
183 for (const auto& var : UndefinedVars(expr)) {
184 auto it = loop_depth_lookup_.find(var.get());
185 if (it != loop_depth_lookup_.end()) {
186 if (prev.has_value()) {
187 prev = {std::min(prev.value().first, it->second.first),
188 std::max(prev.value().second, it->second.second)};
189 } else {
190 prev = it->second;
191 }
192 }
193 }
194
195 return prev;
196 }
197
198 class BufferStoreReplacer : public StmtExprMutator {
199 public:
200 BufferStoreReplacer(std::function<Optional<Stmt>(const BufferStoreNode*)> replace_store,
201 std::function<Optional<Stmt>(const BlockRealizeNode*, const BlockRealize&)>
202 replace_block_realize)
203 : replace_store_(replace_store), replace_block_realize_(replace_block_realize) {}
204
205 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
206 if (auto replacement = replace_store_(op)) {
207 auto store = Downcast<BufferStore>(replacement.value());
208 return StmtExprMutator::VisitStmt_(store.get());
209 } else {
210 return StmtExprMutator::VisitStmt_(op);
211 }
212 }
213
214 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) final {
215 auto realize = Downcast<BlockRealize>(StmtExprMutator::VisitStmt_(op));
216 if (auto replacement = replace_block_realize_(op, realize)) {
217 return replacement.value();
218 } else {
219 return std::move(realize);
220 }
221 }
222
223 private:
224 std::function<Optional<Stmt>(const BufferStoreNode*)> replace_store_;
225 std::function<Optional<Stmt>(const BlockRealizeNode*, const BlockRealize&)>
226 replace_block_realize_;
227 };
228
229 TransformPlan Finalize(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map, IndexMap inverse,
230 PrimExpr padding_predicate, Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
231 if (auto prologue_plan =
232 FinalizeProloguePlan(new_buffer, index_map, inverse, padding_predicate, pad_value);
233 prologue_plan.has_value()) {
234 return prologue_plan.value();
235 } else if (auto replacement_plan = FinalizeReplacementPlan(new_buffer, index_map, inverse,
236 padding_predicate, pad_value);
237 replacement_plan.has_value()) {
238 return replacement_plan.value();
239 } else if (auto epilogue_plan = FinalizeEpiloguePlan(new_buffer, index_map, inverse,
240 padding_predicate, pad_value);
241 epilogue_plan.has_value()) {
242 return epilogue_plan.value();
243 } else {
244 return NoPaddingRequired();
245 }
246 }
247
248 std::optional<ProloguePlan> FinalizeProloguePlan(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
249 IndexMap inverse, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
250 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
251 if (write_info_.size() || is_zero(padding_predicate) || !pad_value.defined()) {
252 return std::nullopt;
253 }
254
255 Array<IterVar> iter_vars;
256 Array<PrimExpr> iter_values;
257 Array<PrimExpr> indices;
258 Map<Var, PrimExpr> loop_indices_to_block_indices;
259 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
260 for (size_t i = 0; i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); i++) {
261 const auto& loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
262 const auto& dim = new_buffer->shape[i];
263 Var block_var("v_" + loop_var->name_hint, loop_var->dtype);
264 IterVar iter_var(Range(0, dim), block_var, kDataPar);
265 loop_indices_to_block_indices.Set(loop_var, block_var);
266 indices.push_back(iter_var->var);
267 iter_vars.push_back(iter_var);
268 iter_values.push_back(loop_var);
269 }
270 padding_predicate = Substitute(std::move(padding_predicate), loop_indices_to_block_indices);
271
272 PrimExpr pad_value_at_index = pad_value.value()->MapIndices(indices)[0];
273 PrimExpr expr = (!padding_predicate) || (BufferLoad(new_buffer, indices) == pad_value_at_index);
274 Stmt stmt = Evaluate(Call(DataType::Bool(), builtin::assume(), {expr}));
275
276 std::stringstream block_name;
277 block_name << "buffer_" << new_buffer->name << "_assumptions";
278 auto read_region = BufferRegion::FromPoint(new_buffer, indices);
279 stmt = BlockRealize(iter_values, Bool(true),
280 Block(iter_vars, {read_region}, {}, block_name.str(), stmt));
281
282 for (size_t rev_i = 0; rev_i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); rev_i++) {
283 size_t i = (inverse->initial_indices.size() - 1) - rev_i;
284 Var loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
285 PrimExpr extent = new_buffer->shape[i];
286 stmt = For(loop_var, 0, extent, ForKind::kSerial, stmt);
287 }
288 return ProloguePlan{stmt};
289 }
290
291 std::optional<ReplacementPlan> FinalizeReplacementPlan(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
292 IndexMap inverse,
293 PrimExpr padding_predicate,
294 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
295 if (write_info_.empty() || is_zero(padding_predicate) || !pad_value.defined()) {
296 return std::nullopt;
297 }
298
299 auto generate_if_then_else_block = [&](const WriteInfo& info) -> Optional<Stmt> {
300 if (!info.contains_row_major_traversal || !pad_value.defined() ||
301 is_zero(padding_predicate)) {
302 return NullOpt;
303 }
304
305 Array<PrimExpr> old_indices = info.store->indices;
306 PrimExpr if_then_else_condition = padding_predicate;
307 Array<PrimExpr> new_indices;
308 for (const auto& var : inverse->initial_indices) {
309 new_indices.push_back(var);
310 }
311
312 auto replace_block_realize =
313 [&]() -> std::function<Optional<Stmt>(const BlockRealizeNode*, const BlockRealize&)> {
314 auto no_change = [](const BlockRealizeNode*, const BlockRealize&) -> Optional<Stmt> {
315 return NullOpt;
316 };
317 if (!info.innermost_block_realize) {
318 return no_change;
319 }
320 if (old_indices.empty()) {
321 return no_change;
322 }
323
324 BlockRealize block_realize = info.innermost_block_realize.value();
325 const auto& block = block_realize->block;
326
327 // Find the block iterators that are used to access the buffer. Must be in the same order
328 // as they appear in the indices.
329 if (block->iter_vars.size() < old_indices.size()) {
330 return no_change;
331 }
332 const auto& iter_vars = block->iter_vars;
333 size_t block_index_start = 0;
334 for (; block_index_start < iter_vars.size() - old_indices.size(); block_index_start++) {
335 if (old_indices[0].same_as(iter_vars[block_index_start]->var)) {
336 break;
337 }
338 }
339 if (block_index_start > iter_vars.size() - old_indices.size()) {
340 return no_change;
341 }
342
343 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_indices.size(); i++) {
344 if (!old_indices[i].same_as(iter_vars[block_index_start + i]->var) ||
345 iter_vars[block_index_start + i]->iter_type != kDataPar) {
346 return no_change;
347 }
348 }
349
350 // If we got to this point, all indices used to access the
351 // buffer are virtual indices defined in the innermost block.
352 // Therefore, generate new virtual indices for iterating over
353 // the post-transform buffer.
354 Array<PrimExpr> new_iter_values; // For BlockRealize
355 Array<IterVar> new_iter_vars; // For Block
356 Array<PrimExpr> new_access_indices; // For BufferStore
357 Map<Var, PrimExpr> loop_var_to_virtual_var; // For updating if_then_else_condition
358
359 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_index_start; i++) {
360 new_iter_vars.push_back(iter_vars[i]);
361 new_iter_values.push_back(block_realize->iter_values[i]);
362 }
363
364 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
365 for (size_t i = 0; i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); i++) {
366 Var var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
367 PrimExpr dim = new_buffer->shape[i];
368 std::stringstream ss;
369 ss << "v_" << var->name_hint;
370 Var virtual_var(ss.str(), var.dtype());
371 new_iter_values.push_back(var);
372 new_iter_vars.push_back(
373 IterVar(Range::FromMinExtent(make_zero(dim.dtype()), dim), virtual_var, kDataPar));
374 new_access_indices.push_back(virtual_var);
375 loop_var_to_virtual_var.Set(var, virtual_var);
376 }
377
378 for (size_t i = block_index_start + old_indices.size(); i < iter_vars.size(); i++) {
379 new_iter_vars.push_back(iter_vars[i]);
380 new_iter_values.push_back(block_realize->iter_values[i]);
381 }
382
383 Map<Var, PrimExpr> old_virtual_var_to_new_virtual_var;
384 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->final_indices.size(), old_indices.size());
385 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_indices.size(); i++) {
386 Var var = Downcast<Var>(old_indices[i]);
387 PrimExpr expr = Substitute(inverse->final_indices[i], loop_var_to_virtual_var);
388 old_virtual_var_to_new_virtual_var.Set(var, expr);
389 }
390
391 if_then_else_condition = Substitute(if_then_else_condition, loop_var_to_virtual_var);
392 new_indices = new_access_indices;
393
394 return [target_realize = info.innermost_block_realize, new_iter_vars, new_iter_values,
395 old_virtual_var_to_new_virtual_var](const BlockRealizeNode* op,
396 const BlockRealize& visited) -> Optional<Stmt> {
397 if (op == target_realize.get()) {
398 Block block = visited->block;
399 block =
400 Downcast<Block>(Substitute(std::move(block), old_virtual_var_to_new_virtual_var));
401 block.CopyOnWrite()->iter_vars = new_iter_vars;
402
403 BlockRealize realize = visited;
404 {
405 auto write_ptr = realize.CopyOnWrite();
406 write_ptr->block = block;
407 write_ptr->iter_values = new_iter_values;
408 }
409 return realize;
410 } else {
411 return NullOpt;
412 }
413 };
414 }();
415
416 bool all_stores_replaced = true;
417 auto replace_store = [&](const BufferStoreNode* op) -> Optional<Stmt> {
418 if (!op->buffer.same_as(info.store->buffer)) {
419 all_stores_replaced = false;
420 return NullOpt;
421 }
422 ICHECK_EQ(old_indices.size(), op->indices.size());
423 ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
424 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_indices.size(); i++) {
425 if (!expr_equal(old_indices[i], op->indices[i])) {
426 all_stores_replaced = false;
427 return NullOpt;
428 }
429 }
430
431 PrimExpr pad_value_at_index = pad_value.value()->MapIndices(new_indices)[0];
432 return BufferStore(new_buffer,
433 if_then_else(if_then_else_condition, pad_value_at_index, op->value),
434 new_indices);
435 };
436
437 BufferStoreReplacer replacer(replace_store, replace_block_realize);
438 Stmt stmt = replacer(info.dependent_loopnest.back()->body);
439 if (!all_stores_replaced) {
440 return NullOpt;
441 }
442
443 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, PrimExpr> var_remap;
444 ICHECK_EQ(info.dependent_loopnest.size(), inverse->final_indices.size());
445 for (size_t i = 0; i < info.dependent_loopnest.size(); i++) {
446 Var var = info.dependent_loopnest[i]->loop_var;
447 PrimExpr expr = inverse->final_indices[i];
448 var_remap[var.get()] = expr;
449 }
450 stmt = Substitute(std::move(stmt), var_remap);
451
452 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
453 for (size_t rev_i = 0; rev_i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); rev_i++) {
454 size_t i = (inverse->initial_indices.size() - 1) - rev_i;
455 Var loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
456 PrimExpr extent = new_buffer->shape[i];
457 stmt = For(loop_var, 0, extent, ForKind::kSerial, stmt);
458 }
459
460 return stmt;
461 };
462
463 Map<For, Stmt> loop_replacements;
464
465 for (const auto& info : write_info_) {
466 if (info.dependent_loopnest.size()) {
467 if (auto opt_stmt = generate_if_then_else_block(info)) {
468 loop_replacements.Set(info.dependent_loopnest[0], opt_stmt.value());
469 }
470 }
471 }
472
473 if (loop_replacements.size()) {
474 return ReplacementPlan{std::move(loop_replacements)};
475 } else {
476 return std::nullopt;
477 }
478 }
479
480 std::optional<EpiloguePlan> FinalizeEpiloguePlan(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
481 IndexMap inverse, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
482 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
483 if (write_info_.empty() || is_zero(padding_predicate) || !pad_value.defined()) {
484 return std::nullopt;
485 }
486
487 Array<IterVar> iter_vars;
488 Array<PrimExpr> iter_values;
489 Array<PrimExpr> indices;
490 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
491 for (size_t i = 0; i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); i++) {
492 const auto& loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
493 const auto& dim = new_buffer->shape[i];
494 Var block_var("v_" + loop_var->name_hint, loop_var->dtype);
495 IterVar iter_var(Range(0, dim), block_var, kDataPar);
496 indices.push_back(iter_var->var);
497 iter_vars.push_back(iter_var);
498 iter_values.push_back(loop_var);
499 }
500
501 PrimExpr pad_value_at_index = pad_value.value()->MapIndices(indices)[0];
502 Stmt stmt = BufferStore(new_buffer, pad_value_at_index, indices);
503
504 std::stringstream block_name;
505 block_name << "buffer_" << new_buffer->name << "_padding";
506 auto write_region = BufferRegion::FromPoint(new_buffer, indices);
507 stmt = BlockRealize(iter_values, padding_predicate,
508 Block(iter_vars, {}, {write_region}, block_name.str(), stmt));
509
510 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
511 for (size_t rev_i = 0; rev_i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); rev_i++) {
512 size_t i = (inverse->initial_indices.size() - 1) - rev_i;
513 Var loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
514 PrimExpr extent = new_buffer->shape[i];
515 stmt = For(loop_var, 0, extent, ForKind::kSerial, stmt);
516 }
517
518 const auto& info = write_info_.back();
519 Stmt insert_after = [&]() -> Stmt {
520 if (info.dependent_loopnest.size()) {
521 return info.dependent_loopnest.front();
522 } else if (info.innermost_block_realize) {
523 return info.innermost_block_realize.value();
524 } else {
525 LOG(FATAL) << "Write occured outside of any block/loop";
526 return Stmt();
527 }
528 }();
529 return EpiloguePlan{insert_after, stmt};
530 }
531
532 struct BindLoopVar {
533 BindLoopVar(TransformLayoutPlanner* self, For for_node)
534 : self_(self), var_(for_node->loop_var) {
535 size_t loop_depth = self_->active_loops_.size();
536 self_->loop_depth_lookup_[var_.get()] = {loop_depth, loop_depth};
537 self_->active_loops_.push_back(std::move(for_node));
538 }
539 ~BindLoopVar() {
540 self_->active_loops_.pop_back();
541 self_->loop_depth_lookup_.erase(var_.get());
542 }
543 BindLoopVar(const BindLoopVar&) = delete;
544 BindLoopVar& operator=(const BindLoopVar&) = delete;
545 BindLoopVar(BindLoopVar&&) = delete;
546 BindLoopVar& operator=(BindLoopVar&&) = delete;
547
548 TransformLayoutPlanner* self_{nullptr};
549 Var var_;
550 };
551
552 struct BindVariableDefinition {
553 BindVariableDefinition() {}
554 BindVariableDefinition(TransformLayoutPlanner* self, Var var, PrimExpr value)
555 : self_(self), var_(var) {
556 if (auto loop_depth = self->LoopDependencyRange(value); loop_depth.has_value()) {
557 self_->loop_depth_lookup_[var_.get()] = loop_depth.value();
558 self_->active_var_bindings_[var_.get()] = Substitute(value, self_->active_var_bindings_);
559 }
560 }
561 ~BindVariableDefinition() {
562 if (self_) {
563 self_->loop_depth_lookup_.erase(var_.get());
564 self_->active_var_bindings_.erase(var_.get());
565 }
566 }
567 BindVariableDefinition(const BindVariableDefinition&) = delete;
568 BindVariableDefinition& operator=(const BindVariableDefinition&) = delete;
569 BindVariableDefinition(BindVariableDefinition&& other) : BindVariableDefinition() {
570 swap(other);
571 }
572 BindVariableDefinition& operator=(BindVariableDefinition&& other) {
573 swap(other);
574 return *this;
575 }
576 void swap(BindVariableDefinition& other) {
577 std::swap(self_, other.self_);
578 std::swap(var_, other.var_);
579 }
580
581 TransformLayoutPlanner* self_{nullptr};
582 Var var_;
583 };
584
585 struct BindBlockRealize {
586 BindBlockRealize(TransformLayoutPlanner* self, BlockRealize block_realize) : self_(self) {
587 ICHECK_EQ(block_realize->iter_values.size(), block_realize->block->iter_vars.size());
588 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_realize->iter_values.size(); i++) {
589 bound_vars_.emplace_back(self, block_realize->block->iter_vars[i]->var,
590 block_realize->iter_values[i]);
591 }
592 cache_ = std::move(block_realize);
593 std::swap(self_->innermost_block_realize_, cache_);
594 }
595 ~BindBlockRealize() { std::swap(self_->innermost_block_realize_, cache_); }
596 BindBlockRealize(const BindBlockRealize&) = delete;
597 BindBlockRealize& operator=(const BindBlockRealize&) = delete;
598 BindBlockRealize(BindBlockRealize&&) = delete;
599 BindBlockRealize& operator=(BindBlockRealize&&) = delete;
600
601 TransformLayoutPlanner* self_{nullptr};
602 Optional<BlockRealize> cache_;
603 std::vector<BindVariableDefinition> bound_vars_;
604 };
605
606 struct WriteInfo {
607 // The BufferStore object
608 BufferStore store;
609
610 // The block realize that contains the store, if any.
611 Optional<BlockRealize> innermost_block_realize;
612
613 // The nested loops whose values contribute to the indices used in
614 // the store. Not all loop variables in the loopnest need to
615 // contribute, but the first and last must.
616 std::vector<For> dependent_loopnest;
617
618 // Whether the padding could be represented as a tir::if_then_else
619 // node. This requires that the surrounding loop iterators
620 // iterate over all pre-transformation buffer axes, that there are
621 // no data dependencies between loop iterations, and that
622 bool contains_row_major_traversal{false};
623 };
624
625 /*! \brief Collected information about each BufferStore */
626 std::vector<WriteInfo> write_info_;
627
628 /*! \brief The loop iterators surrounding the current node
629 *
630 * The outermost loop iterator is `active_loops_.front()`, and the
631 * innermost loop iterator is `active_loops_.back()`.
632 *
633 * Used to fill the `WriteInfo::dependent_loopnest` field.
634 */
635 std::vector<For> active_loops_;
636
637 /*! \brief Lookup for the outer/inner loops
638 *
639 * Used to fill the `WriteInfo::dependent_loopnest` field.
640 */
641 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::pair<size_t, size_t>> loop_depth_lookup_;
642
643 /*! \brief The variable mappings that are currently in-scope
644 *
645 * Used to determine whether the indices of a BufferStore are a
646 * row-major traversal, even if they are rebound in let/block
647 * mappings.
648 */
649 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, PrimExpr> active_var_bindings_;
650
651 /*! \brief The innermost BlockRealize surrounding the current node
652 *
653 * Used to fill the `WriteInfo::innermost_block_realize` field..
654 */
655 Optional<BlockRealize> innermost_block_realize_{NullOpt};
656
657 /*! \brief The buffer to be replaced */
658 Buffer old_buffer_;
659};
660
661class TransformLayoutRewriter : private arith::IRMutatorWithAnalyzer {
662 public:
663 /*!
664 * \brief Rewrite the access to the buffer after the transformation
665 * \param scope_stmt The parent statement that contains all accesses to the target buffer
666 * \param old_buffer The target buffer before transformation
667 * \param new_buffer The new buffer after transformation
668 * \param index_map The transformation applied to the buffer
669 * \return The new AST rooting at the original parent scope and the map from the old block to the
670 * new block
671 */
672 static std::pair<Stmt, Map<Block, Block>> Rewrite(
673 const Block& scope_stmt, const Buffer& old_buffer, const Buffer& new_buffer,
674 const IndexMap& index_map, const IndexMap& inverse, const PrimExpr& padding_predicate,
675 const Optional<IndexMap>& pad_value) {
676 auto plan = TransformLayoutPlanner::Plan(scope_stmt, old_buffer, new_buffer, index_map, inverse,
677 padding_predicate, pad_value);
678
679 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
680 TransformLayoutRewriter rewriter(old_buffer, new_buffer, index_map, plan, &analyzer);
681 Block result = Downcast<Block>(rewriter(scope_stmt));
682 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::ProloguePlan>(&plan)) {
683 auto write_ptr = result.CopyOnWrite();
684 write_ptr->body = SeqStmt({plan_ptr->prologue, write_ptr->body});
685 }
686 return {result, rewriter.block_sref_reuse_};
687 }
688
689 private:
690 TransformLayoutRewriter(const Buffer& old_buffer, const Buffer& new_buffer,
691 const IndexMap& index_map,
692 const TransformLayoutPlanner::TransformPlan& plan,
693 arith::Analyzer* analyzer)
694 : IRMutatorWithAnalyzer(analyzer),
695 old_buffer_(old_buffer),
696 new_buffer_(new_buffer),
697 index_map_(index_map),
698 plan_(plan),
699 buffer_data_to_buffer_{{new_buffer->data, new_buffer}} {}
700
701 void RewriteBufferAccess(Buffer* buffer, Array<PrimExpr>* indices) {
702 *buffer = new_buffer_;
703 *indices = index_map_->MapIndices(*indices);
704 (*indices).MutateByApply(
705 [&](const PrimExpr& e) { return SimplifyNonTrivialExpr(e, analyzer_); });
706 }
707
708 using Parent = arith::IRMutatorWithAnalyzer;
709 using Parent::VisitExpr_;
710 using Parent::VisitStmt_;
711
712 Stmt VisitStmt(const Stmt& stmt) final {
713 Stmt output = Parent::VisitStmt(stmt);
714 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::EpiloguePlan>(&plan_)) {
715 if (plan_ptr->insert_after.same_as(stmt)) {
716 return SeqStmt({output, plan_ptr->new_block});
717 }
718 }
719 return output;
720 }
721
722 Stmt VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) final {
723 // Some replacements may include the original string, such as
724 // replacing `loop` with `{loop, post_proc}`. In this case, avoid
725 // infinite recursion.
726
727 For node = GetRef<For>(op);
728 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::ReplacementPlan>(&plan_)) {
729 auto it = plan_ptr->replacements.find(node);
730 if (it != plan_ptr->replacements.end()) {
731 return VisitStmt((*it).second);
732 }
733 }
734 return Parent::VisitStmt_(op);
735 }
736
737 PrimExpr VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
738 BufferLoad buffer_load = Downcast<BufferLoad>(Parent::VisitExpr_(op));
739 if (buffer_load->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
740 auto* n = buffer_load.CopyOnWrite();
741 RewriteBufferAccess(&n->buffer, &n->indices);
742 }
743 return std::move(buffer_load);
744 }
745
746 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
747 BufferStore buffer_store = Downcast<BufferStore>(Parent::VisitStmt_(op));
748 if (buffer_store->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
749 auto* n = buffer_store.CopyOnWrite();
750 RewriteBufferAccess(&n->buffer, &n->indices);
751 }
752 return std::move(buffer_store);
753 }
754
755 void RewriteAccessRegion(Array<BufferRegion>* old_access_regions,
756 const Array<BufferRegion>& infered_access_regions) {
757 auto fmutate = [this, &infered_access_regions](const BufferRegion& buffer_region) {
758 if (buffer_region->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
759 ICHECK(infered_access_regions.size() == 1);
760 return infered_access_regions[0];
761 }
762 return buffer_region;
763 };
764 (*old_access_regions).MutateByApply(fmutate);
765 }
766
767 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BlockNode* op) final {
768 Block block = Downcast<Block>(Parent::VisitStmt_(op));
769 auto infered_access_regions = GetBlockReadWriteRegion(block, buffer_data_to_buffer_);
770 auto* n = block.CopyOnWrite();
771 RewriteAccessRegion(&n->reads, infered_access_regions[0]);
772 RewriteAccessRegion(&n->writes, infered_access_regions[1]);
773 n->alloc_buffers.MutateByApply([this](const Buffer& buffer) {
774 if (buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
775 return new_buffer_;
776 } else {
777 return buffer;
778 }
779 });
780 block_sref_reuse_.Set(GetRef<Block>(op), block);
781 return std::move(block);
782 }
783
784 const Buffer& old_buffer_;
785 const Buffer& new_buffer_;
786 const IndexMap& index_map_;
787 const TransformLayoutPlanner::TransformPlan& plan_;
788 Map<Var, Buffer> buffer_data_to_buffer_;
789 Map<Block, Block> block_sref_reuse_;
790};

964void TransformLayout(ScheduleState self, const StmtSRef& block_sref, int buffer_index,
965 BufferIndexType buffer_index_type, const IndexMap& index_map,
966 const Optional<IndexMap>& pad_value) {
967 // Step 1: Input handling and error checking
968 const BlockNode* block_ptr = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
969 Buffer old_buffer =
970 GetNthAccessBuffer(self, GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), buffer_index, buffer_index_type);
971 auto [defining_site_sref, is_alloc] = GetBufferDefiningSite(block_sref, old_buffer);
972 if (defining_site_sref.defined() && !is_alloc) {
973 throw BufferIsSubregionError(self->mod, old_buffer);
974 }
975 if (pad_value) {
976 if (pad_value.value()->final_indices.size() != 1) {
977 throw TransformationPaddingIndexMapError(self->mod, pad_value.value());
978 }
979 if (pad_value.value()->final_indices[0]->dtype != old_buffer->dtype) {
980 throw TransformationPaddingTypeError(self->mod, old_buffer, pad_value.value());
981 }
982
983 TransformationPaddingExpressionError::Check(self->mod, old_buffer, pad_value.value());
984 }
985
986 StmtSRef scope_sref = defining_site_sref.defined()
987 ? defining_site_sref.value()
988 : GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
989 const BlockNode* scope_block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
990
991 auto [inverse, padding_predicate] = [&]() {
992 Array<Range> region;
993 for (const auto& dim : old_buffer->shape) {
994 region.push_back(Range::FromMinExtent(make_zero(dim.dtype()), dim));
995 }
996 return index_map.NonSurjectiveInverse(region);
997 }();
998
999 bool has_padding = !is_zero(padding_predicate);
1000 if (has_padding && !pad_value.defined()) {
1001 throw TransformationIntroducesPaddingError(self->mod, old_buffer, index_map, padding_predicate);
1002 }
1003
1004 // Step 2: Infer the shape of the new buffer
1005 Buffer new_buffer = old_buffer;
1006 new_buffer.CopyOnWrite()->shape = index_map->MapShape(old_buffer->shape);
1007
1008 // Step 3: Rewrite BufferLoad/BufferStore access indices, block read/write regions, and block
1009 // alloc_buffers.
1010 auto [new_stmt, block_sref_reuse] =
1011 TransformLayoutRewriter::Rewrite(GetRef<Block>(scope_block), old_buffer, new_buffer,
1012 index_map, inverse, padding_predicate, pad_value);
1013 Block new_scope_block = Downcast<Block>(new_stmt);
1014
1015 // Step 4: Rewrite buffer_map of the PrimFunc if necessary.
1016 if (!defining_site_sref.defined()) {
1017 GlobalVar g_var;
1018 GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, scope_block, &g_var);
1019 IRModuleNode* new_mod = self->mod.CopyOnWrite();
1020 MapNode* new_map = new_mod->functions.CopyOnWrite();
1021 PrimFunc ref_new_func = Downcast<PrimFunc>(std::move(new_map->at(g_var)));
1022 PrimFuncNode* new_func = ref_new_func.CopyOnWrite();
1023 MapNode* new_buffer_map = new_func->buffer_map.CopyOnWrite();
1024 for (auto it = new_buffer_map->begin(); it != new_buffer_map->end(); ++it) {
1025 if ((*it).second.same_as(old_buffer)) {
1026 (*it).second = new_buffer;
1027 }
1028 }
1029 new_map->at(g_var) = std::move(ref_new_func);
1030 }
1031
1032 // Step 4: Replace the scope block with the new block
1033 self->Replace(scope_sref, new_scope_block, block_sref_reuse);
1034}
1035
1036/*!
1037 * \brief Detect the block iter type assoicated with the expression
1038 *
1039 * This function collects block iters in the expression and check if the block iters have the same
1040 * iter type. The detected iter type is the iter type of the block iters in the expression
1041 * if they have the same iter type, otherwise the detected iter type will be kOpaque.
1042 *
1043 * \param expr The expression
1044 * \param block_iter_type_map The mapping from block iter to iter type
1045 * \return The detected block iter type
1046 */
1047IterVarType DetectNewBlockIterType(
1048 const PrimExpr& expr,
1049 const std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType>& block_iter_type_map) {
1050 IterVarType result{kOpaque};
1051 bool found = false;
1052 PostOrderVisit(expr, [&](const ObjectRef& obj) {
1053 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
1054 auto it = block_iter_type_map.find(var);
1055 if (it != block_iter_type_map.end()) {
1056 if (!found) {
1057 found = true;
1058 result = it->second;
1059 } else if (result != it->second) {
1060 result = kOpaque;
1061 return false;
1062 }
1063 }
1064 }
1065 return true;
1066 });
1067 return result;
1068}

1152
1153void TransformBlockLayout(ScheduleState self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
1154 const IndexMap& index_map) {
1155 const BlockNode* block_ptr = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1156 const Block& block = GetRef<Block>(block_ptr);
1157 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
1158
1159 // Step 1: Collect outer loops and loop vars
1160 Array<StmtSRef> loops = GetLoops(block_sref); // outer loops of the block
1161 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> loop_vars; // loop vars of the outer loops
1162 for (const StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
1163 CheckLoopStartsWithZero(self, loop_sref, &analyzer);
1164 loop_vars.emplace(loop_sref->StmtAs<ForNode>()->loop_var.get());
1165 }
1166
1167 // Step 2: Check the all outer loops have a single child and the block bindings are trivial (all
1168 // binding values are loop vars)
1169 StmtSRef scope_sref{nullptr}; // the scope statement for replacement
1170 if (!loops.empty()) {
1171 scope_sref = loops.front();
1172 CheckGetSingleChildBlockRealizeOnSRefTree(self, loops.front());
1173 } else {
1174 scope_sref = block_sref;
1175 }
1176
1177 BlockRealize block_realize = GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref);
1178 CheckBlockHasTrivialBinding(self, block_sref);
1179
1180 // Step 3: Collect information of block iter vars
1181 Array<PrimExpr> block_vars; // iter_var->var of each block iter
1182 Map<Var, Range> block_iter_dom; // domain of block iter
1183 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType> block_iter_type; // iter type of block iter
1184
1185 Array<PrimExpr>
1186 block_iter_range_array; // array of block iter extents in the same order as block iters
1187 for (const auto& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1188 block_vars.push_back(iter_var->var);
1189 block_iter_dom.Set(iter_var->var, iter_var->dom);
1190 block_iter_type[iter_var->var.get()] = iter_var->iter_type;
1191 ICHECK(is_zero(iter_var->dom->min));
1192 block_iter_range_array.push_back(iter_var->dom->extent);
1193 }
1194
1195 // Step 4: Apply the IndexMap to block iters.
1196 IndexMapNotApplicableToBlockIterError::Check(self->mod, block, index_map);
1197 Array<PrimExpr> transformed_block_iters = index_map->MapIndices(block_vars);
1198 Array<PrimExpr> new_block_iter_range = index_map->MapShape(block_iter_range_array);
1199
1200 // Step 5: Create the new block after transformation.
1201
1202 // Step 5.1: Create new block iters. After applying the IndexMap f to block iters ax_0, ..., ax_n,
1203 // create block iter each expression in f(ax_0, ..., ax_n).
1204 Array<IterVar> new_block_iters; // new block iters
1205 Array<PrimExpr> new_block_vars; // iter_var->var of new block iters
1206 for (size_t i = 0; i < transformed_block_iters.size(); ++i) {
1207 Var new_block_var{"v" + std::to_string(i), transformed_block_iters[i]->dtype};
1208 new_block_vars.push_back(new_block_var);
1209 IterVarType iter_type = DetectNewBlockIterType(transformed_block_iters[i], block_iter_type);
1210 if (iter_type == kOpaque) {
1211 throw OpaqueNewIterTypeError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), transformed_block_iters[i]);
1212 }
1213 auto dtype = new_block_var.dtype();
1214 new_block_iters.push_back(IterVar(
1215 /*dom=*/Range::FromMinExtent(make_zero(dtype), new_block_iter_range[i]),
1216 /*var=*/std::move(new_block_var), /*iter_type=*/iter_type));
1217 }
1218
1219 // Step 5.2: Update the block body. Use the inverse map f^{-1} to replace the original block iters
1220 // in the body.
1221 Map<Var, PrimExpr> inverse_subst_map;
1222 // Construct the inverse map
1223 {
1224 Array<Range> initial_ranges;
1225 for (const PrimExpr& extent : block_iter_range_array) {
1226 initial_ranges.push_back(Range::FromMinExtent(make_const(extent.dtype(), 0), extent));
1227 }
1228 IndexMap inverse_index_map{nullptr};
1229 try {
1230 inverse_index_map = index_map.Inverse(initial_ranges);
1231 } catch (...) {
1232 throw NotBijectiveAffineIndexMapError(self->mod, index_map);
1233 }
1234
1235 Array<PrimExpr> inversed_new_block_vars = inverse_index_map->MapIndices(
1236 new_block_vars); // old block vars written in terms of new block vars
1237
1238 for (int i = 0, n = block_vars.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1239 inverse_subst_map.Set(Downcast<Var>(block_vars[i]), inversed_new_block_vars[i]);
1240 }
1241 }
1242 Block new_block = Downcast<Block>(Substitute(GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), inverse_subst_map));
1243 new_block.CopyOnWrite()->iter_vars = new_block_iters;
1244 new_block = Downcast<Block>(BlockBufferAccessSimplifier::Simplify(new_block, &analyzer));
1245
1246 // Step 5.3: Create outer loops for each new block iter.
1247
1248 // Make new loop vars
1249 Array<PrimExpr> new_loop_vars;
1250 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(new_block_iters.size()); ++i) {
1251 new_loop_vars.push_back(Var("ax" + std::to_string(i), new_block_iters[i]->var.dtype()));
1252 }
1253
1254 // Make new block realize
1255 BlockRealizeNode* new_block_realize = block_realize.CopyOnWrite();
1256 new_block_realize->iter_values = new_loop_vars;
1257 new_block_realize->block = new_block;
1258
1259 // Generate outer loops
1260 Stmt body = GetRef<Stmt>(new_block_realize);
1261 for (int i = static_cast<int>(new_loop_vars.size()) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1262 body = For(Downcast<Var>(new_loop_vars[i]), 0, new_block_iter_range[i], ForKind::kSerial,
1263 std::move(body));
1264 }
1265
1266 // Step 6: Do the actual replacement
1267 self->Replace(scope_sref, body, {{block, new_block}});
1268}
1269
1270class BufferAxisSeparatorMutator : private ReplaceBufferMutator {
1271 public:
1272 static Block Mutate(const Block& scope_block, const Buffer& old_buffer, Buffer new_buffer,
1273 Map<Block, Block>* block_sref_reuse) {
1274 BufferAxisSeparatorMutator mutator(old_buffer, std::move(new_buffer), block_sref_reuse);
1275 return Downcast<Block>(mutator.VisitStmt(scope_block));
1276 }
1277
1278 private:
1279 BufferAxisSeparatorMutator(const Buffer& old_buffer, Buffer new_buffer,
1280 Map<Block, Block>* block_sref_reuse)
1281 : ReplaceBufferMutator(old_buffer, new_buffer, block_sref_reuse) {}
1282
1283 MatchBufferRegion VisitMatchBufferRegion(const MatchBufferRegion& match_buffer) final {
1284 auto it = buffer_var_map_.find(match_buffer->source->buffer->data.get());
1285 if (it != buffer_var_map_.end()) {
1286 const Buffer& new_source_buffer = it->second;
1287 Buffer new_target_buffer = match_buffer->buffer;
1288 new_target_buffer.CopyOnWrite()->axis_separators = new_source_buffer->axis_separators;
1289 if (new_target_buffer->shape.size() != new_source_buffer->shape.size()) {
1290 LOG(WARNING)
1291 << "Target buffer in match_buffer doesn't have the same dimensionality as its source "
1292 "buffer. `axis_separators` for the target buffer might be incorrect.";
1293 }
1294 buffer_var_map_[new_target_buffer->data.get()] = new_target_buffer;
1295 return MatchBufferRegion(new_target_buffer,
1296 BufferRegion(new_source_buffer, match_buffer->source->region));
1297 }
1298 return match_buffer;
1299 }
1300};
1301
1302void SetAxisSeparator(ScheduleState self, const StmtSRef& block_sref, int buffer_index,
1303 BufferIndexType buffer_index_type, const Array<IntImm>& axis_separators) {
1304 const BlockNode* block_ptr = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1305 Buffer old_buffer =
1306 GetNthAccessBuffer(self, GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), buffer_index, buffer_index_type);
1307 auto [defining_site_sref, is_alloc] = GetBufferDefiningSite(block_sref, old_buffer);
1308 if (defining_site_sref.defined() && !is_alloc) {
1309 throw BufferIsSubregionError(self->mod, old_buffer);
1310 }
1311
1312 StmtSRef scope_sref = defining_site_sref.defined()
1313 ? defining_site_sref.value()
1314 : GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
1315 const BlockNode* scope_block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
1316
1317 // Step 1: Check and update axis_separators of the buffer.
1318 Buffer new_buffer = old_buffer;
1319 new_buffer.CopyOnWrite()->axis_separators = axis_separators;
1320
1321 Map<Block, Block> block_sref_reuse;
1322
1323 // Step 2: Rewrite alloc_buffer of the block or buffer_map of the PrimFunc.
1324 Block new_scope_block = BufferAxisSeparatorMutator::Mutate(GetRef<Block>(scope_block), old_buffer,
1325 new_buffer, &block_sref_reuse);
1326 if (!defining_site_sref.defined()) {
1327 // mutate buffer_map of the PrimFunc
1328 GlobalVar g_var;
1329 GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, scope_block, &g_var);
1330 IRModuleNode* new_mod = self->mod.CopyOnWrite();
1331 MapNode* new_map = new_mod->functions.CopyOnWrite();
1332 PrimFunc ref_new_func = Downcast<PrimFunc>(std::move(new_map->at(g_var)));
1333 PrimFuncNode* new_func = ref_new_func.CopyOnWrite();
1334 MapNode* new_buffer_map = new_func->buffer_map.CopyOnWrite();
1335 for (auto it = new_buffer_map->begin(); it != new_buffer_map->end(); ++it) {
1336 if ((*it).second.same_as(old_buffer)) {
1337 (*it).second = new_buffer;
1338 }
1339 }
1340 new_map->at(g_var) = std::move(ref_new_func);
1341 }
1342
1343 // Step 4: Replace the scope block with the new block
1344 self->Replace(scope_sref, new_scope_block, block_sref_reuse);
1345}
